-- CEZ's Pocerady Plant Is Priority for Czech Coal: HN Says
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2012-12-10T07:21:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-10/cez-s-pocerady-plant-is-priority-for-czech-coal-hn-says.html
Czech Coal AS sees the purchase of
 CEZ AS (CEZ) ’s Pocerady power plant as a priority and continues talks
with the electricity producer on the sale, Hospodarske Noviny
reported, citing Czech Coal co-founder Jan Dienstl.  Czech Coal’s current offer for Pocerady expires on Dec. 18,
the newspaper said, citing an interview with Dienstl. While the
coal producer hasn’t renewed its offer for Chvaletice, another
of CEZ’s coal-fired plants, it’s still interested in purchasing
it, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ladka Bauerova in Prague at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  